a structure is dropped.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to read raw binary data without interpretation, then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"encoding argument."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function is available in GLib on Windows, too, but you should","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"avoid using it on Windows. The domain of file descriptors and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sockets overlap. There is no way for GLib to know which one you mean"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in case the argument you pass to this function happens to be both a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"valid file descriptor and socket. If that happens a warning is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"issued, and GLib assumes that it is the file descriptor you mean.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref\/unixnew(unix:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a new "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets."}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Type Method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib12IOChannelRefV7unixNew0D0ACSgSi_tFZ","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","title":"unixNew(unix:)","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"sta